import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from PlateAnalysis import PlateDataset
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import re


Plate = PlateDataset('20191206_1percentTriton.CSV')


CompoundMap = dict(zip(range(1,25),['Lauric Acid']*6 + \
                       ['Arachadionic Acid']*6 + \
                       ['Palmitic Acid']*6 + \
                       ['4-Phenylimidazole']*6))

metrics = pd.DataFrame([],columns = ['Plate','Block','Kd','Vmax','R_sq','Noise'])

for j in range(1,25):

    NormalizedTraces, DifferenceSpec, DiffDiff = Plate.AnalysisPipeline_1(j)
    print('Plate: {} \t Compound: {}'.format(Plate.plate_data,CompoundMap[j]))
    Plate.PlotTrace(NormalizedTraces)
    Plate.PlotTrace(DifferenceSpec)
    K,percentDMSO, Vol = 3, 5, 20
    concs = Plate.CalculateCompoundConcs(K,Vol,percentDMSO)
    km, vmax, loss = Plate.FitMichaelisMenten(concs, DiffDiff)
    Plate.PlotMichaelesMenten(DiffDiff,concs,\
                          km, vmax, loss,\
                          'Plate: {} \t Compound: {}'.format(Plate.plate_data,CompoundMap[j]))
    noise = Plate.Noise(NormalizedTraces)

    temp = pd.DataFrame([[str(Plate.plate_data),j,CompoundMap[j],km,vmax,1-loss, noise]],\
                                  columns = ['Plate','Block','Compound','Kd','Vmax','R_sq','Noise'])
    metrics = metrics.append(temp,sort = True)

metrics.reset_index(inplace = True,drop=True)
metrics.to_csv('Triton1Percent_metrics.csv')

from PathLength import PlatePathlength

K_kpiDMSOTriton =  0.15866462890000002


plt.figure(figsize = (10,5))

data = PlatePathlength('20191206_pathlength.CSV',K_kpiDMSOTriton)
plengths = data.Pathlength()
plt.hist(plengths, bins = 15, alpha = 0.7)

plt.title('Estimated pathlengths')
plt.legend(['KPi ','KPi and Triton'])
plt.xlabel('Pathlength (mm)')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.xlim((0,3))
plt.show()
